# Common Mistakes

## Forgetting SSH Before Enabling UFW

This is one of the most common mistakes on remote Linux servers.

Always allow SSH first.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Allowing the Wrong Port

Applications frequently use custom ports.

Verify the listening port using:

``` bash
ss -tulpn
```

before creating firewall rules.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Confusing TCP and UDP

Allowing TCP traffic does not automatically allow UDP traffic.

Always verify which transport protocol the application uses.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Best Practices

-   Enable the firewall on production servers.
-   Allow only required services.
-   Use predefined application profiles when available.
-   Review firewall rules regularly.
-   Test access after every firewall change.

